[
    [span_1](start_span){ "question": "1. Consider the following statements:\n1. Under the Government of India Act, 1919, the Indian Legislature was made more representative and for the first time bicameral.\n2. The Government of India Act, 1935, prescribed a federation taking the Provinces and the Indian States as units.\nWhich of the statements given above is/are correct?", "options": ["(a) Only 1", "(b) Only 2", "(c) Both 1 and 2", "(d) Neither 1 nor 2"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "The 1919 Act introduced bicameralism at the center, and the 1935 Act proposed an All-India Federation of provinces and princely states[span_1](end_span)." },
    { "question": "2. Which of the following are the principal features of the Government of India Act, 1919?\n1. Introduction of dyarchy in the executive government of the Provinces.\n2. Introduction of separate communal electorates for Muslims.\n3. Devolution of legislative authority by the Centre to the Provinces.\n4. [span_2](start_span)Expansion and reconstitution of Central and Provincial Legislatures.", "options": ["(a) 1, 2 and 3", "(b) 2, 3 and 4", "(c) 1, 2 and 4", "(d) 1, 3 and 4"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "Separate electorates for Muslims were introduced in 1909, not 1919[span_2](end_span)." },
    { "question": "3. Consider the following statements:\n1. The first Public Service Commission in India was set up in the year 1926, on the recommendation of the Lee Commission on the Superior Civil Services in India.\n2. [span_3](start_span)The Government of India Act, 1935, provided for setting up of public service commissions at both the federal and provincial levels.", "options": ["(a) Only 1", "(b) Only 2", "(c) Both 1 and 2", "(d) Neither 1 nor 2"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "Both statements are correct regarding the evolution of civil services commissions[span_3](end_span)." },
    { "question": "4. [span_4](start_span)Which one of the following Acts provided the setting up of a Board of Control in Britain, through which the British Government could fully control the British East India Company's civil, military and revenue affairs in India?", "options": ["(a) Regulating Act of 1773", "(b) Pitt's India Act of 1784", "(c) Charter Act of 1833", "(d) Government of India Act of 1858"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "Pitt’s India Act of 1784 established the Board of Control to supervise the Company's affairs[span_4](end_span)." },
    { "question": "5. Match List I (Acts) with List II (Provisions):\nA. 1935 Act - 3. Provincial autonomy\nB. 1909 Act - 5. Separate electorate for Muslims\nC. 1919 Act - 4. Dyarchy in provinces\nD. [span_5](start_span)1858 Act - 1. Transfer of power to British crown", "options": ["(a) A-1, B-4, C-2, D-3", "(b) A-3, B-5, C-4, D-1", "(c) A-1, B-5, C-4, D-3", "(d) A-3, B-4, C-2, D-1"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "Correct matches: 1935 (Provincial Autonomy), 1909 (Communal Electorate), 1919 (Dyarchy), 1858 (Crown Rule)[span_5](end_span)." },
    { "question": "6. [span_6](start_span)Partially responsible governments in the provinces were established under which one of the following Acts?", "options": ["(a) The Government of India Act, 1919", "(b) The Government of India Act, 1935", "(c) Indian Councils Act, 1909", "(d) Indian Councils Act, 1892"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "Dyarchy introduced by the 1919 Act established partial responsibility in provinces[span_6](end_span)." },
    { "question": "7. [span_7](start_span)The initial idea of recruitment on merit principle can be traced to the:", "options": ["(a) Lee Commission", "(b) Macaulay Committee", "(c) Islington Commission", "(d) Maxwell Committee"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "The Macaulay Committee (1854) introduced the merit-based competitive exam system[span_7](end_span)." },
    { "question": "8. [span_8](start_span)During the period of British rule in India, the rules made under which one of the following were known as the Devolution Rules?", "options": ["(a) Government of India Act, 1919", "(b) Indian Councils Act, 1909", "(c) Indian Councils Act, 1892", "(d) Government of India Act, 1935"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "The 1919 Act introduced Devolution Rules to separate central and provincial subjects[span_8](end_span)." },
    { "question": "9. [span_9](start_span)Which one of the following pairs is correctly matched?", "options": ["(a) 1892 Act : Principle of Election", "(b) 1909 Act : Responsible Government", "(c) 1919 Act : Provincial Autonomy", "(d) 1935 Act : Dyarchy in States"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "The 1892 Act introduced a limited and indirect use of election in filling non-official seats[span_9](end_span)." },
    { "question": "10. [span_10](start_span)Assertion (A): Notwithstanding the introduction of Provincial Autonomy, the 1935 Act retained control of the Central Government over Provinces.\nReason (R): The Governor was required to act in his discretion in certain matters under the control of the Governor-General.", "options": ["(a) Both A and R are true and R is correct explanation", "(b) Both A and R are true but R is not correct explanation", "(c) A is true but R is false", "(d) A is false but R is true"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "Provincial autonomy was limited by the discretionary powers of the Governor, supervised by the center[span_10](end_span)." },
    { "question": "11. [span_11](start_span)In the Federation established by the Act of 1935, residuary powers were given to the:", "options": ["(a) Federal Legislature", "(b) Provincial Legislature", "(c) Governor General", "(d) Provincial Governor"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "The 1935 Act vested residuary powers in the Governor-General[span_11](end_span)." },
    { "question": "12. Match List I with List II:\nA. 1858 Act - 2. Secretary of State\nB. 1861 Act - 3. Legislative devolution\nC. 1909 Act - 5. Morley-Minto Reforms\nD. [span_12](start_span)1919 Act - 4. Dyarchy in Provinces", "options": ["(a) A-1, B-2, C-3, D-4", "(b) A-2, B-3, C-5, D-4", "(c) A-3, B-4, C-5, D-1", "(d) A-2, B-3, C-4, D-1"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "Correct matches for historical constitutional developments[span_12](end_span)." },
    { "question": "13. [span_13](start_span)The Government of India Act, 1919, was based upon:", "options": ["(a) Morley-Minto Reforms", "(b) Montague-Chelmsford Report", "(c) Ramsay McDonald Award", "(d) Nehru Report"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "The 1919 reforms are known as the Montagu-Chelmsford Reforms[span_13](end_span)." },
    { "question": "14. [span_14](start_span)Under which one of the following Acts, was the Communal Electorate System introduced by the British in India, for the first time?", "options": ["(a) Government of India Act, 1909", "(b) Government of India Act, 1919", "(c) Indian Councils Act of 1861", "(d) Indian Councils Act of 1892"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "Communal representation for Muslims was introduced by the 1909 Act (Minto-Morley)[span_14](end_span)." },
    { "question": "15. What were the salient features of the Government of India Act, 1935?\n1. Abolition of Council of India\n2. Dyarchy at the Centre\n3. Abolition of Dyarchy in the States\n4. [span_15](start_span)Establishment of Federal Court", "options": ["(a) 2 and 3", "(b) 1, 2 and 3", "(c) 1, 3 and 4", "(d) 1, 2, 3 and 4"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "All listed were key features of the 1935 Act[span_15](end_span)." },
    { "question": "16. Match features with Acts:\nA. Federal Scheme - 3. 1935 Act\nB. Dyarchy in Provinces - 4. 1919 Act\nC. Communal representation - 1. 1909 Act\nD. [span_16](start_span)Rigid centralization - 2. 1861 Act", "options": ["(a) A-2, B-1, C-4, D-3", "(b) A-3, B-4, C-1, D-2", "(c) A-2, B-4, C-1, D-3", "(d) A-3, B-1, C-4, D-2"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "Matching specific constitutional features to their origin acts[span_16](end_span)." },
    { "question": "17. Who among the following was the Finance Minister of India in the Interim Government during 1946-1947?", "options": ["(a) R.K. [span_17](start_span)Shanmukham Chetty", "(b) John Mathai", "(c) Liaquat Ali Khan", "(d) Chintamanrao Deshmukh"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "Liaquat Ali Khan represented the Muslim League as Finance Minister in the Interim Government[span_17](end_span)." },
    { "question": "18. [span_18](start_span)Which one of the following Acts laid the foundation of the British Administration in India?", "options": ["(a) Regulating Act, 1773", "(b) Pitt's India Act, 1784", "(c) Indian Councils Act, 1861", "(d) Indian Councils Act, 1892"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "The 1773 Act was the first step by the British Government to regulate the East India Company[span_18](end_span)." },
    { "question": "19. Match Provisions with Acts:\nA. Gov-Gen of India - 1. 1833 Act\nB. Dyarchy in India - 4. 1919 Act\nC. All-India Federation - 3. 1935 Act\nD. [span_19](start_span)EIC to Crown - 2. 1858 Act", "options": ["(a) A-1, B-4, C-3, D-2", "(b) A-2, B-3, C-4, D-1", "(c) A-1, B-3, C-4, D-2", "(d) A-2, B-4, C-3, D-1"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "Key matches for major legislative milestones[span_19](end_span)." },
    { "question": "20. Who among the following was the first Law Minister of India?", "options": ["(a) Jawahar Lal Nehru", "(b) Maulana Abul Kalam Azad", "(c) Dr. BR Ambedkar", "(d) T Krishnamachari"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "Dr. B.R. [span_20](start_span)Ambedkar was the first Law Minister of independent India[span_20](end_span)." },
    { "question": "21. [span_21](start_span)With reference to the period of British Rule in India, Indian Statutory Commission is popularly known as:", "options": ["(a) Cabinet Mission", "(b) Hunter Commission", "(c) Sadlar Commission", "(d) Simon Commission"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "The Simon Commission was the Statutory Commission appointed to report on the 1919 Act[span_21](end_span)." },
    { "question": "22. [span_22](start_span)During the British Rule in India, who was the first Indian to be appointed as Law Member of the Governor General's Council?", "options": ["(a) Raja Kishori Lal Goswami", "(b) Motilal Nehru", "(c) Satyendra Sinha", "(d) Tej Bahadur Sapru"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "Satyendra Prasad Sinha was the first Indian to join the Viceroy’s Executive Council[span_22](end_span)." }
]
